  "prompt": "I'm new to Quora. What does it mean when someone says they are following me?",
  "response": "When someone says they are following you on Quora, it means that they have chosen to subscribe to your activity on the platform. By following you, they will see your questions, answers, comments, and other contributions in their Quora feed. This allows them to stay updated on your content and engage with your posts more easily.\n\nHere's a bit more detail on what following entails on Quora:\n\n1. **Content Visibility**: Your new questions, answers, and comments will appear in their feed, making it easier for them to see and interact with your content.\n\n2. **Notifications**: Depending on their notification settings, they might receive notifications when you post new content or engage in discussions.\n\n3. **Engagement**: Followers can upvote, comment on, or share your content, increasing its visibility and sparking discussions.\n\n4. **Profile Access**: They can easily access your profile to learn more about your interests and expertise.\n\nFollowing someone on Quora is a way for users to curate their feed with content from people they find interesting or valuable. It's a great way to build a community and connect with like-minded individuals on the platform.",
